<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-12-18T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-12-18T11:00:00-05:00" n="904" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d904">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">390D.1124 Bitzer, John Andre/7:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-18T16:00:00+00:00">December 18, 1939—4
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 18—2:38 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2991. Your 1313, October 26, 6 p.m., and my 2690, November 8, 5 p.m.
                                Foreign Office advises that reasons for detention of John Andre
                                Bitzer have been communicated to Consul at Beirut.<note n="23" xml:id="d904fn23">There is no indication in Department files
                                    that any supporting evidence for the expulsion of Mr. Bitzer was
                                    ever given; the Bitzers were forced to leave Syria, December 7,
                                    1939.</note></p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>